          href='https://montessoritools.org/'
          heading='Montessori Virtual Tools'
          subheading='A collection of free tools for Montessori educators.'
          imagePath='/src/assets/montessori-child.png'
          altText='Child holding a tablet with Montessori tools on the screen'
          class='w-full sm:w-1/2'
        />
        <ProjectCard
          href='https://github.com/mhornbacher/zoom-to-control4'
          heading='Zoom to Control 4'
          subheading='Small persistent TCP server for controlling Control4 from Zoom Rooms.'
          imagePath='/src/assets/zoom-to-control-4.png'
          altText='Zoom to Control 4 Logo AI generated image'
          class='w-full sm:w-1/2'
        />
      </div>
    </Section>

    <Section title='Experience'>
      <Card
        heading='Kiddom'
        subheading='Senior Product Engineer'
        date='June 2023 - Present'
        imagePath='/src/assets/kiddom.svg'
        altText='Kiddom Logo'
        imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16'
      >
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          Dipping my toe back into the product-focused world at a fast-paced, mission-driven startup in the EdTech
          space. In this role I was directly responsible for delivering critical features that secured NYC adoption as
          well as improving WCAG accessibility across the platform.
        </p>
      </Card>
      <Card
        heading='Block / AfterPay'
        subheading='Senior Lead Platform Engineer'
        date='October 2021 - April 2023'
        imagePath='/src/assets/block.svg'
        altText='Block Logo'
        imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16 dark:invert'
      >
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          Joined the Block family through the acquisition of AfterPay, leading a team of 5 engineers to build out
          "CashKite" an in house CI/CD platform infrastructure platform on AWS that mitigated supply-chain attacks that
          the industry is only now starting to seriously grapple with.
        </p>
        <!-- <ul class='text-muted-foreground ml-4 list-disc'>
          <li>Delivered critical features that secured state-level adoption.</li>
          <li>Improved accessibility (AA/AAA WCAG) by leading an internal hackathon.</li>
        </ul> -->
      </Card>
      <Card
        heading='NeonOne'
        subheading='Senior Product Engineer'
        date='June 2023 - Present'
        imagePath='/src/assets/neonone.png'
        altText='NeonOne Logo'
        imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16 dark:invert dark:brightness-0 dark:sepia dark:saturate-100 dark:hue-rotate-180'
      >
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          After a small detour into consulting I joined my friends at Rallybound (now NeonOne) leading a rotating team
          of 5 engineers building out new features and improving the core fundraising platform .NET framework on Azure.
        </p>
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          Our greatest successes were supporting the NFL's draft day event(s) as well as transitioning our payments to
          .NET Core without downtime or a single dropped charge to maintain PCI compliance.
        </p>
      </Card>
      <Card
        heading='Tzivos Hashem'
        subheading='Devops Engineer'
        date='September 2017 - December 2018'
        imagePath='/src/assets/tzivoshashem.png'
        altText='Tzivos Hashem Logo'
        imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16'
      >
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          Transitioned from seasonal work to my first job as the sole software engineer at local non-profit managing all
          IT and web infrastructure, in addition to developing new features on top of a legacy PHP codebase.
        </p>
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          In this role I am proud to have introduced modern software practices such as CI/CD, Git, and VirtualBox for
          local development. In addition to introducing React.JS to improve our admin panel performance by multiple
          orders of magnitude.
        </p>
      </Card>
      <Card
        heading='Leiders Sukkah'
        subheading='Webmaster & Wholesale Manager'
        date='September 2015 - September 2017'
        imagePath='/src/assets/leiders-sukkah.svg'
        altText='Leiders Sukkah Logo'
        imageClass='h-12 w-auto md:-left-16'
      >
        <p class='text-muted-foreground'>
          Started as a seasonal worker during the Sukkot holiday, quickly promoted to webmaster for the 1990s Perl site,
          all internal IT as well as managing our wholesale accounts around the world.
        </p>
      </Card>
    </Section>

